tasks.description:
Extend `apps/server/src/services/marketplace/package-fetcher.ts` so it can read marketplace.json documents and package contents from local `file://` URLs in addition to its existing git/HTTPS support. This is the foundation that lets the personal marketplace (which lives at `~/.dork/personal-marketplace/`) be treated like any other marketplace source.

## Why

The personal marketplace (task 1.2) registers itself with `MarketplaceSourceManager` using a source string like `file:///Users/foo/.dork/personal-marketplace`. The existing `PackageFetcher.fetchMarketplaceJson()` derives the URL by stripping `.git` and appending `/raw/main/marketplace.json` (works for GitHub/GitLab) and then calls global `fetch()`, which does NOT handle `file://` URLs portably. We need a small switch at the top of the fetcher path that detects `file://` and reads from disk via `node:fs/promises` instead.

## Files to modify

- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace/package-fetcher.ts` — add `isFileUrl()` helper, branch in `fetchMarketplaceJson()` and `fetchFromGit()` for `file://`.
- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace/__tests__/package-fetcher.test.ts` — add coverage for `file://` source handling.

## Implementation

1. Add a private helper:

```typescript
/** True when `source` is a `file://` URL pointing at a local directory. */
function isFileUrl(source: string): boolean {
  return source.startsWith('file://');
}

/** Convert a `file://` URL into an absolute filesystem path. */
function fileUrlToPath(source: string): string {
  return new URL(source).pathname;
}
```

2. In `fetchMarketplaceJson()`, branch before the existing HTTP fetch path:

```typescript
async fetchMarketplaceJson(source: MarketplaceSource): Promise<MarketplaceJson> {
  if (isFileUrl(source.source)) {
    return this.readLocalMarketplaceJson(source);
  }
  // ... existing HTTP path unchanged
}

private async readLocalMarketplaceJson(source: MarketplaceSource): Promise<MarketplaceJson> {
  const root = fileUrlToPath(source.source);
  const manifestPath = path.join(root, 'marketplace.json');
  let raw: string;
  try {
    raw = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf-8');
  } catch (err) {
    throw new Error(
      `Failed to read local marketplace at ${manifestPath}: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`
    );
  }
  const parsed = parseMarketplaceJson(raw);
  if (!parsed.ok) {
    throw new Error(parsed.error);
  }
  // Cache the result so the resolver and search tools can read it back.
  await this.cache.writeMarketplace(source.name, parsed.marketplace);
  return parsed.marketplace;
}
```

3. In `fetchFromGit()`, add an early return when the resolved git URL is a `file://` URL — instead of cloning, return the directory directly. The personal marketplace stores packages at `<root>/packages/<name>/` so the resolver should populate `gitUrl` to point at that directory.

```typescript
async fetchFromGit(opts: FetchPackageOptions): Promise<FetchedPackage> {
  if (isFileUrl(opts.gitUrl)) {
    const localPath = fileUrlToPath(opts.gitUrl);
    return { path: localPath, commitSha: 'local', fromCache: true };
  }
  // ... existing clone logic unchanged
}
```

4. Imports needed at the top of `package-fetcher.ts`: `import { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';` and `import path from 'node:path';`.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `fetchMarketplaceJson()` reads `file://` sources from disk via `fs.readFile`, parses with `parseMarketplaceJson`, caches the result.
- [ ] `fetchFromGit()` returns the local directory immediately when the gitUrl is `file://`, with `commitSha: 'local'` and `fromCache: true`.
- [ ] Errors when the file is missing return a clear `Failed to read local marketplace at <path>: ...` message.
- [ ] Existing HTTP/git path is unchanged for non-`file://` sources (test it does not regress).
- [ ] New tests cover: missing file, invalid JSON, valid file://, fetchFromGit with file://.

Create `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/personal-marketplace.ts` that ensures the personal marketplace exists at `${dorkHome}/personal-marketplace/` on every server boot, and registers it as a marketplace source via `MarketplaceSourceManager` so the existing fetcher/resolver/search pipelines can see it.

## Directory layout produced

```
${dorkHome}/personal-marketplace/
├── marketplace.json    # Personal registry index (empty plugins[] on creation)
├── README.md           # User-facing intro
├── packages/           # Empty directory; agent-scaffolded packages land here
└── .gitignore          # Default-ignored, user can `git init` manually
```

The `marketplace.json` shape mirrors the dorkos-community marketplace:

```json
{
  "name": "personal",
  "description": "Your personal DorkOS marketplace — packages you scaffold or maintain locally",
  "plugins": []
}
```

## Files to create

- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/personal-marketplace.ts`
- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/__tests__/personal-marketplace.test.ts`

## Public API

```typescript
export interface PersonalMarketplaceDeps {
  /** Resolved DorkOS data directory (see `.claude/rules/dork-home.md`). */
  dorkHome: string;
  /** Source manager used to register the personal marketplace. */
  sourceManager: MarketplaceSourceManager;
  /** Logger for diagnostic output. */
  logger: Logger;
}

/**
 * Ensure the personal marketplace exists at `${dorkHome}/personal-marketplace/`
 * and is registered as a marketplace source. Idempotent — safe to call on every
 * server boot.
 */
export async function ensurePersonalMarketplace(deps: PersonalMarketplaceDeps): Promise<void>;

/** The on-disk path of the personal marketplace root. */
export function personalMarketplaceRoot(dorkHome: string): string;

/** Source name used when registering the personal marketplace. */
export const PERSONAL_MARKETPLACE_NAME = 'personal' as const;
```

## Implementation

```typescript
import { mkdir, readFile, writeFile, access } from 'node:fs/promises';
import path from 'node:path';
import type { Logger } from '@dorkos/shared/logger';
import type { MarketplaceSourceManager } from '../marketplace/marketplace-source-manager.js';

export const PERSONAL_MARKETPLACE_NAME = 'personal' as const;

export function personalMarketplaceRoot(dorkHome: string): string {
  return path.join(dorkHome, 'personal-marketplace');
}

const DEFAULT_README = `# Personal Marketplace

This directory is your personal DorkOS marketplace. Packages you scaffold via
` + '`marketplace_create_package`' + ` or copy here manually become available to
` + 'your DorkOS install and to any AI agent that talks to it via MCP.

' + 'Packages live under ' + '`packages/`' + ' and are listed in ' + '`marketplace.json`' + '.
';

const DEFAULT_GITIGNORE = `# Default: ignore everything. Run \`git init\` and edit this file if you want to track contents.
*
!.gitignore
`;

function defaultMarketplaceJson() {
  return {
    name: PERSONAL_MARKETPLACE_NAME,
    description: 'Your personal DorkOS marketplace — packages you scaffold or maintain locally',
    plugins: [],
  };
}

export async function ensurePersonalMarketplace(deps: PersonalMarketplaceDeps): Promise<void> {
  const root = personalMarketplaceRoot(deps.dorkHome);
  const packagesDir = path.join(root, 'packages');
  const manifestPath = path.join(root, 'marketplace.json');
  const readmePath = path.join(root, 'README.md');
  const gitignorePath = path.join(root, '.gitignore');

  await mkdir(packagesDir, { recursive: true });

  // Seed marketplace.json on first run only.
  try {
    await access(manifestPath);
  } catch {
    await writeFile(
      manifestPath,
      JSON.stringify(defaultMarketplaceJson(), null, 2) + '\n',
      'utf-8'
    );
  }

  // README and .gitignore are best-effort seeds.
  try { await access(readmePath); } catch { await writeFile(readmePath, DEFAULT_README, 'utf-8'); }
  try { await access(gitignorePath); } catch { await writeFile(gitignorePath, DEFAULT_GITIGNORE, 'utf-8'); }

  // Register as a marketplace source if not already present.
  const existing = await deps.sourceManager.get(PERSONAL_MARKETPLACE_NAME);
  if (!existing) {
    await deps.sourceManager.add({
      name: PERSONAL_MARKETPLACE_NAME,
      source: `file://${root}`,
      enabled: true,
    });
    deps.logger.info('[personal-marketplace] registered source', { root });
  }
}
```

## Wiring (separate from this task — see task 4.1)

The call site lands in `apps/server/src/index.ts` after `ensureBuiltinMarketplaceExtension(dorkHome)` runs. That edit is part of task 4.1; this task only delivers the function and tests.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `ensurePersonalMarketplace()` creates the directory tree on first call.
- [ ] Idempotent: re-running on an existing directory does not throw, does not overwrite `marketplace.json`, README, or .gitignore.
- [ ] Registers a `personal` source with `file://` URL when not already present.
- [ ] When the source is already registered, no `add()` call is made (verify via `MarketplaceSourceManager.get()` + spy).
- [ ] Tests use `mkdtemp` for an isolated `dorkHome` and pass an in-memory or stub `MarketplaceSourceManager`.
- [ ] Tests cover: fresh install path, idempotent re-run, marketplace.json shape, source registration.
- [ ] Per `.claude/rules/dork-home.md`, `dorkHome` is a required parameter — no fallback to `os.homedir()`.

Create `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/confirmation-provider.ts` defining the `ConfirmationProvider` interface used by the install/uninstall/create-package MCP tools, plus three concrete implementations: in-app, out-of-band token, and auto-approve. The provider lets the same MCP tool work in different contexts (DorkOS UI, external Claude Code, CI).

## Files to create

- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/confirmation-provider.ts`
- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/__tests__/confirmation-provider.test.ts`

## Interface

```typescript
import type { PermissionPreview } from '../marketplace/types.js';

/** Result of a confirmation request. Discriminated by `status`. */
export type ConfirmationResult =
  | { status: 'approved' }
  | { status: 'declined'; reason?: string }
  | { status: 'pending'; token: string };

/** Generic confirmation provider that gates mutation tools. */
export interface ConfirmationProvider {
  /**
   * Request user confirmation for an install/uninstall operation. Implementations
   * may surface a prompt synchronously (in-app UI), return a token for out-of-band
   * approval (external MCP clients), or auto-approve when explicitly configured.
   */
  requestInstallConfirmation(req: {
    packageName: string;
    marketplace: string;
    operation: 'install' | 'uninstall' | 'create-package';
    preview?: PermissionPreview;
  }): Promise<ConfirmationResult>;

  /**
   * Look up a previously issued confirmation token. Used when an external MCP
   * client re-calls `marketplace_install` after the user approved out-of-band.
   */
  resolveToken(token: string): Promise<ConfirmationResult>;
}
```

## Implementations

### 1. AutoApproveConfirmationProvider

```typescript
export class AutoApproveConfirmationProvider implements ConfirmationProvider {
  async requestInstallConfirmation(): Promise<ConfirmationResult> {
    return { status: 'approved' };
  }
  async resolveToken(): Promise<ConfirmationResult> {
    return { status: 'approved' };
  }
}
```

Used when `process.env.MARKETPLACE_AUTO_APPROVE === '1'` or in unit tests that want to skip the confirmation gate.

### 2. TokenConfirmationProvider

Issues short-lived (5 min, single-use, scoped) tokens for external MCP clients. The agent receives `{ status: 'pending', token }` and re-calls the tool with the token after the user approves in the DorkOS UI.

```typescript
import { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';

interface PendingConfirmation {
  token: string;
  packageName: string;
  marketplace: string;
  operation: 'install' | 'uninstall' | 'create-package';
  createdAt: number;
  resolvedTo?: 'approved' | 'declined';
  declineReason?: string;
}

export class TokenConfirmationProvider implements ConfirmationProvider {
  private readonly pending = new Map<string, PendingConfirmation>();
  private readonly ttlMs = 5 * 60 * 1000;

  async requestInstallConfirmation(req: {
    packageName: string;
    marketplace: string;
    operation: 'install' | 'uninstall' | 'create-package';
  }): Promise<ConfirmationResult> {
    const token = randomUUID();
    this.pending.set(token, {
      token,
      packageName: req.packageName,
      marketplace: req.marketplace,
      operation: req.operation,
      createdAt: Date.now(),
    });
    return { status: 'pending', token };
  }

  /** Called by the DorkOS UI when the user clicks Approve / Decline. */
  approve(token: string): void {
    const entry = this.pending.get(token);
    if (entry) entry.resolvedTo = 'approved';
  }

  decline(token: string, reason?: string): void {
    const entry = this.pending.get(token);
    if (entry) {
      entry.resolvedTo = 'declined';
      entry.declineReason = reason;
    }
  }

  async resolveToken(token: string): Promise<ConfirmationResult> {
    const entry = this.pending.get(token);
    if (!entry) return { status: 'declined', reason: 'Unknown or expired token' };
    if (Date.now() - entry.createdAt > this.ttlMs) {
      this.pending.delete(token);
      return { status: 'declined', reason: 'Token expired' };
    }
    if (entry.resolvedTo === 'approved') {
      this.pending.delete(token); // single-use
      return { status: 'approved' };
    }
    if (entry.resolvedTo === 'declined') {
      this.pending.delete(token);
      return { status: 'declined', reason: entry.declineReason };
    }
    return { status: 'pending', token };
  }
}
```

### 3. InAppConfirmationProvider

For in-process callers (the DorkOS server-side install path) — delegates to a callback that the host wires to the existing `InstallConfirmationDialog` pattern from spec 03. Returns `approved` / `declined` synchronously.

```typescript
export interface InAppConfirmationCallback {
  (req: {
    packageName: string;
    marketplace: string;
    operation: 'install' | 'uninstall' | 'create-package';
    preview?: PermissionPreview;
  }): Promise<{ status: 'approved' } | { status: 'declined'; reason?: string }>;
}

export class InAppConfirmationProvider implements ConfirmationProvider {
  constructor(private readonly callback: InAppConfirmationCallback) {}

  async requestInstallConfirmation(req): Promise<ConfirmationResult> {
    return this.callback(req);
  }

  async resolveToken(): Promise<ConfirmationResult> {
    return { status: 'declined', reason: 'In-app provider does not issue tokens' };
  }
}
```

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `ConfirmationProvider` interface defined with `requestInstallConfirmation()` and `resolveToken()`.
- [ ] `AutoApproveConfirmationProvider` always returns `approved`.
- [ ] `TokenConfirmationProvider` issues UUID tokens, supports approve/decline out of band, expires tokens after 5 minutes, single-use semantics (token is removed after first resolve to approved/declined).
- [ ] `InAppConfirmationProvider` delegates to a callback synchronously.
- [ ] Tests cover: token issuance, token expiry, approve+resolve, decline+resolve, unknown token handling, single-use enforcement, auto-approve always succeeds.

Create `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/marketplace-mcp-tools.ts` containing the dependency interface that every marketplace MCP tool consumes plus the `registerMarketplaceTools()` helper called from `apps/server/src/services/core/mcp-server.ts`. This task ships only the wiring scaffold — the actual tool handlers ship in phases 2/3/5/6.

## Files to create

- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/marketplace-mcp-tools.ts`
- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/__tests__/marketplace-mcp-tools.test.ts`

## Interface

```typescript
import type { McpServer } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js';
import type { Logger } from '@dorkos/shared/logger';
import type { InstallerLike } from '../marketplace/marketplace-installer.js';
import type { MarketplaceSourceManager } from '../marketplace/marketplace-source-manager.js';
import type { PackageFetcher } from '../marketplace/package-fetcher.js';
import type { MarketplaceCache } from '../marketplace/marketplace-cache.js';
import type { UninstallFlow } from '../marketplace/flows/uninstall.js';
import type { ConfirmationProvider } from './confirmation-provider.js';

/**
 * Dependency bundle for the marketplace MCP tools. Mirrors the existing
 * `McpToolDeps` pattern in `services/runtimes/claude-code/mcp-tools/types.ts`
 * but is scoped to the marketplace surface so tool handlers do not need to
 * pull in unrelated services.
 */
export interface MarketplaceMcpDeps {
  /** Resolved DorkOS data directory (`.claude/rules/dork-home.md`). */
  dorkHome: string;
  /** Installer orchestrator used by `marketplace_install` and `marketplace_get`. */
  installer: InstallerLike;
  /** Source manager for `marketplace_list_marketplaces`. */
  sourceManager: MarketplaceSourceManager;
  /** Fetcher used to refresh marketplace.json before search. */
  fetcher: PackageFetcher;
  /** Cache used by search/get when reading marketplace.json. */
  cache: MarketplaceCache;
  /** Uninstall flow used by `marketplace_uninstall`. */
  uninstallFlow: UninstallFlow;
  /** Confirmation provider that gates mutation tools. */
  confirmationProvider: ConfirmationProvider;
  /** Structured logger. */
  logger: Logger;
}

/**
 * Register every marketplace MCP tool against an existing `McpServer` instance.
 * Called from `createExternalMcpServer()` in `services/core/mcp-server.ts`
 * after the existing tool registrations.
 *
 * The handlers themselves are imported from sibling files (`tool-search.ts`,
 * `tool-get.ts`, etc.) and registered here so the call site sees one helper
 * instead of seven imports.
 */
export function registerMarketplaceTools(server: McpServer, deps: MarketplaceMcpDeps): void;
```

## Implementation skeleton

```typescript
export function registerMarketplaceTools(server: McpServer, deps: MarketplaceMcpDeps): void {
  // Tool registrations land here as phases 2–6 ship. For phase 1 we only
  // ship the no-op helper so downstream phases can land independently and
  // the dispatch table is in one file.
  void server;
  void deps;
}
```

Later phases append `server.tool('marketplace_search', ..., createSearchHandler(deps))` and equivalent registrations as each handler lands.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `MarketplaceMcpDeps` type is exported and can be constructed at the call site.
- [ ] `registerMarketplaceTools()` is callable, type-checks, and is a no-op until later phases plug in handlers.
- [ ] Tests assert that `registerMarketplaceTools()` does not throw when called with a stub `McpServer` and a stub deps bundle.
- [ ] No imports from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` (this surface is the external MCP, not the internal Claude Code SDK path).

Create `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/tool-search.ts` exporting `createSearchHandler(deps: MarketplaceMcpDeps)` and a Zod input schema. Register the tool in `marketplace-mcp-tools.ts` (task 1.4 file) so it appears in the external `/mcp` server.

## Files to create

- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/tool-search.ts`
- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/__tests__/tool-search.test.ts`

## Files to modify

- `apps/server/src/services/marketplace-mcp/marketplace-mcp-tools.ts` — add the registration in `registerMarketplaceTools()`.

## Tool definition

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';
import type { MarketplaceJsonEntry } from '@dorkos/marketplace';
import type { MarketplaceMcpDeps } from './marketplace-mcp-tools.js';

export const SearchInputSchema = {
  query: z.string().optional().describe('Free-text search across name/description/tags'),
  type: z.enum(['agent', 'plugin', 'skill-pack', 'adapter']).optional(),
  category: z.string().optional(),
  tags: z.array(z.string()).optional(),
  marketplace: z
    .string()
    .optional()
    .describe('Restrict to a specific marketplace source'),
  limit: z.number().int().min(1).max(100).default(20),
};

export const SearchInputZodSchema = z.object(SearchInputSchema);
export type SearchInput = z.infer<typeof SearchInputZodSchema>;
```

## Handler implementation

```typescript
export function createSearchHandler(deps: MarketplaceMcpDeps) {
  return async (args: SearchInput) => {
    const allMarketplaces = await deps.sourceManager.list();
    const filtered = args.marketplace
      ? allMarketplaces.filter((s) => s.name === args.marketplace)
      : allMarketplaces.filter((s) => s.enabled);

    const allEntries: (MarketplaceJsonEntry & { marketplace: string })[] = [];
    for (const source of filtered) {
      try {
        const json = await deps.fetcher.fetchMarketplaceJson(source);
        for (const entry of json.plugins) {
          allEntries.push({ ...entry, marketplace: source.name });
        }
      } catch (err) {
        deps.logger.warn('[marketplace_search] failed to fetch marketplace.json', {
          marketplace: source.name,
          error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),
        });
      }
    }

    let results = allEntries;
    if (args.type) {
      results = results.filter((r) => (r.type ?? 'plugin') === args.type);
    }
    if (args.category) {
      results = results.filter((r) => r.category === args.category);
    }
    if (args.tags?.length) {
      const wanted = args.tags;
      results = results.filter((r) => wanted.some((t) => r.tags?.includes(t)));
    }
    if (args.query) {
      const q = args.query.toLowerCase();
      results = results.filter(
        (r) =>
          r.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||
          (r.description ?? '').toLowerCase().includes(q) ||
          (r.tags ?? []).some((t) => t.toLowerCase().includes(q))
      );
    }

    return {
      content: [
        {
          type: 'text' as const,
          text: JSON.stringify(
            {
              results: results.slice(0, args.limit).map((r) => ({
                name: r.name,
                type: r.type ?? 'plugin',
                description: r.description,
                category: r.category,
                tags: r.tags,
                marketplace: r.marketplace,
                featured: r.featured,
              })),
              total: results.length,
            },
            null,
            2
          ),
        },
      ],
    };
  };
}
```

## Registration (in `marketplace-mcp-tools.ts`)

```typescript
import { createSearchHandler, SearchInputSchema } from './tool-search.js';

// inside registerMarketplaceTools()
server.tool(
  'marketplace_search',
  'Search the DorkOS marketplace for installable packages (agents, plugins, skill packs, adapters). ' +
    'Returns matching entries from every enabled marketplace source. ' +
    'Filters: type (agent/plugin/skill-pack/adapter), category, tags, marketplace, query (free-text).',
  SearchInputSchema,
  createSearchHandler(deps)
